## How to work this file

Only WHAT + live state lives here. The usage rules — maintenance contract, per-item dispatch table, gate reporting package, optional section shapes, plan quality audit — live in `process_checklist.md` → "Working the plan" (mandatory reading at every iteration start; single HOW owner). The archive rule that bounds this file is part of the gate package there (gate-triggered, never time-based).

## Status legend

- `[ ]` — not started.
- `[~]` — **exists but not verified**: built in some form, but incomplete, unhardened, or not behavior-verified on the truth surface.
- `[x]` — done **and** verified: behavior confirmed on the rendered truth surface, per-change gates satisfied (validator + tier-2 verifier; paired test + decision_log entry where stake-tagged).
- `🧑` prefix — user-only manual verification: the agent CANNOT check this box; only the user can, after personally performing the step.

