## Progress-triggered chores (automatic — never user-triggered, never time-based)

No chore fires on a calendar — time-based checks are how things silently never run. Every chore hangs off a PROGRESS EVENT the agent always observes, and records the event it last ran at (a commit hash or gate name — never a date), so "trigger fired but chore didn't run" is mechanically checkable at iteration start.

| Chore | Fires on (progress event) | Last ran at |
|---|---|---|
| Dependency audit (ecosystem `audit` command); patch or EXCEPTIONS-log high-severity | manifest/lockfile changed (same PR — see verification ladder) AND every milestone gate | <commit / gate> |
| `EXCEPTIONS.md` retirement review *(delete row if not generated)* — expired-waiver flagging is already event-owned by the verifier, which reads EXCEPTIONS.md on every dispatch | every milestone gate | <gate> |
| Canary calibration — verifier must flag `canary/known-bad-example.md`; GREEN = broken verifier *(delete row if not generated)* | every milestone gate, BEFORE trusting that gate's verifier verdict | <gate> |
| Pitfall-register retirement audit (rule-retirement procedure) *(delete row if not generated)* | register hits its 200-line cap, OR every 3rd milestone gate (count gate-log entries) | <gate> |

